race.description: Greg Horan Construction Pty Ltd Handicap (Bm58+)
race.comment: BUSTER'S GIRL (10) couldn't hold on last start in a CL2 here last start after finding the front in running. Drawn better this time and Azzopardi replaces the apprentice hoop. Out to 1200m shouldn't be an issue and if she can dictate the speed up front, she'll be hard to mow down. MIDNIGHT RUSH (8) stepped out to 1400m last start and couldn't reel in his rivals, ending up 3.8L off the winner. Back to 1200m now looks a good move and the claim of Catarino gets him down in the weights. Should land close to the speed and be there when it matters. ELITE FIGHTER (6) missed at Pinjarra last start over the mile when $6 chance in a Bm44. He drops back to country level today however and he's a course and distance winner in the past. Yuill replaces the apprentice hoop and he won't be far away. OREGON HIKER (4) was too good last start and can repeat the dose. BELLINI MISS (1) can be in the finish on resumption.
